=========

| **Topic**          | **Description**                                                                                                      |
| ------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Full Form**      | Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM)                                                                                        |
| **Definition**     | LSTM is a special type of Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) designed to remember information for a long period of time. |
| **Purpose**        | To solve the **Vanishing Gradient Problem** found in traditional RNNs.                                               |
| **Memory**         | Uses a **Cell State** to store long-term information.                                                                |
| **Key Components** | Forget Gate, Input Gate, Cell State, Output Gate.                                                                    |
| **Applications**   | Machine Translation, Text Generation, Speech Recognition, Sentiment Analysis, Time Series Forecasting.               |


==============

Why LSTM is Needed?

| **RNN**                                  | **LSTM**                                         |
| ---------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| Remembers only recent information.       | Remembers both recent and long-term information. |
| Suffers from vanishing gradient.         | Solves the vanishing gradient problem.           |
| Performance decreases on long sequences. | Performs well on long sequences.                 |


