=========

Main Components of LSTM

| **Component**           | **Purpose**                                         |
| ----------------------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| **Input (Xt)**          | Current input word or value.                        |
| **Hidden State (Ht-1)** | Information from the previous time step.            |
| **Cell State (Ct)**     | Long-term memory carried through the sequence.      |
| **Forget Gate**         | Decides what old information to remove from memory. |
| **Input Gate**          | Decides what new information to store.              |
| **Output Gate**         | Decides what information to send as the output.     |


===========

Step-by-Step Workflow

| **Step** | **Operation**                                   |
| -------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| 1        | Receive current input (`Xt`).                   |
| 2        | Receive previous hidden state (`Ht-1`).         |
| 3        | Forget Gate removes unnecessary information.    |
| 4        | Input Gate stores important new information.    |
| 5        | Update the Cell State.                          |
| 6        | Output Gate produces the current output (`Ht`). |

===========

Forget Gate
Purpose

Removes unnecessary information.

Formula

ft = σ(Wf × [Ht-1, Xt] + bf)

Example

Sentence:
I went to the bank to deposit money.

Forget Gate remembers that
"bank" means a financial institution,
not a river bank.
Input Gate
Purpose

Stores new useful information.

Formula

it = σ(Wi × [Ht-1, Xt] + bi)

Example

Current word:
money

Input Gate stores
"money" as an important word.
Cell State
Purpose

Stores long-term memory.

Formula

Ct = ft × Ct-1 + it × C̃t

Example

Previous Memory
↓

Bank
Money
Deposit

↓

Updated Memory

Bank
Money
Deposit
Loan
Output Gate
Purpose

Produces the final output.

Formula

Ot = σ(Wo × [Ht-1, Xt] + bo)

Ht = Ot × tanh(Ct)
