============

Advantages

| **Advantage**             | **Description**                                                     |
| ------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Long-Term Memory          | Remembers information over long sequences.                          |
| Better Accuracy           | More accurate than a standard RNN on sequence tasks.                |
| Solves Vanishing Gradient | Maintains useful gradients during training.                         |
| Suitable for NLP          | Excellent for translation, sentiment analysis, and text generation. |

==========

Disadvantages

| **Disadvantage**     | **Description**                                              |
| -------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Complex Architecture | Uses multiple gates, making it more complex than RNN.        |
| Slower Training      | More computations per time step than a standard RNN.         |
| Higher Memory Usage  | Requires more memory due to additional gates and cell state. |

===========

RNN vs LSTM

| **Feature**          | **RNN**    | **LSTM**              |
| -------------------- | ---------- | --------------------- |
| Memory               | Short-term | Long-term             |
| Vanishing Gradient   | Yes        | No (greatly reduced)  |
| Long Sequences       | Poor       | Excellent             |
| Gates                | No         | Forget, Input, Output |
| Translation Accuracy | Moderate   | High                  |


=============

STM (Long Short-Term Memory) is a special type of Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) designed to process sequential data 
while remembering important information over long periods. It uses three gates—Forget Gate, 
Input Gate, and Output Gate—along with a Cell State to control what information is removed, stored, and passed to the next step.
This design helps overcome the vanishing gradient problem of traditional RNNs, making LSTM highly effective for applications 
such as language translation, speech recognition, sentiment analysis, and time-series forecasting.

